weather.description: Chance for showers.
Rain likely for most of the game, doesn’t look particularly heavy, but still wet.
Winds around 15-20mph sustained with stronger gusts.

Winds around 15-20mph sustained with stronger gusts. We also have some rain in the forecast, wouldn't shock me to see heavy rain at some point (early?), but this is typical Miami weather where even if it does pour for a time, it's unlikely to stick around all game (and there's an equally likely chance they dodge the heavy rain completely).

Off and on light rain looks likely, potentially we could see moderate rainfall at times. I would say it's not too dissimilar from the TN game yesterday, the bulk of which was played in light rain (occasionally moderate rain). Both that game and this game had/have light winds, and I just don't think light rain and light winds is enough of a factor to seriously impact a game. Maybe a slight bump down to offense, but I think even that it a stretch... worth noting that the "similar weather game" in Tennessee yesterday went for a combined 78 points. General rule, unless it's windy or absolutely pouring, don't stress.
